+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WJ4Kq3hdwLqF5KNKwoeKY7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue\n     2→\n     3→Implement the core of the task queue: the ability to add tasks and retrieve them in first-in, first-out order.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- The queue should accept a payload (any data) when a task is added, and return a task object.\n     8→- Each task must have a unique identifier (e.g., UUID), a status, and a creation timestamp.\n     9→- New tasks start in a \"pending\" state.\n    10→- Retrieving the next task should return the oldest pending task and transition it to a \"processing\" state.\n    11→- If no tasks are available, retrieval should return `null`.\n    12→- There should be a way to check how many tasks are waiting.\n    13→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2107b12e-f12a-4d0c-bc47-bb3ab39302b3","uuid":"4c264fb1-6014-499f-ae07-40809380f101","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/phases/phase-01.md","content":"# Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue\n\nImplement the core of the task queue: the ability to add tasks and retrieve them in first-in, first-out order.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- The queue should accept a payload (any data) when a task is added, and return a task object.\n- Each task must have a unique identifier (e.g., UUID), a status, and a creation timestamp.\n- New tasks start in a \"pending\" state.\n- Retrieving the next task should return the oldest pending task and transition it to a \"processing\" state.\n- If no tasks are available, retrieval should return `null`.\n- There should be a way to check how many tasks are waiting.\n","numLines":13,"startLine":1,"totalLines":13}}}
