+- A shutdown operation should signal the system to stop accepting new tasks.
+- After shutdown is initiated, attempting to add new tasks should produce an error.
+- The shutdown should wait for all currently-processing tasks to finish, up to a configurable timeout.
+- If processing tasks do not complete within the timeout, they should be force-cancelled.
+- Callbacks can be registered to run during the shutdown process.
+- The shutdown should produce a summary indicating how many tasks completed, how many were force-cancelled, and how long the shutdown took.
+- Calling shutdown multiple times should be safe and return the same result.
+- If no tasks are processing, shutdown should complete immediately.
